description: From New Latin phytolacca, from Ancient Greek φῠτόν (phutón, “plant”) + Italian lacca (“crimson lake”).

entries.meaning: (botany) Any of the genus Phytolacca of herbaceous plants; the poke or pokeweed. [from 18th c.]
examples: Phytolacca or Pokeweed is a domestic Plant in Virginia and New York, grows in all their Plantations.
